AFRICAN HORSE SICKNESS - BOTSWANA: OIE
**************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Thu 3 Jun 2004
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <arodriguezm@SaludFMV.org>
Source: OIE alert messages, 31 May 2004 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/Messages/040601BWA.htm>

African horse sickness in Botswana
----------------------------------
(Date of previous outbreak of African horse sickness in Botswana
reported to the OIE: August 2003).
Information received on 31 May 2004 from Dr Micus Chiwasanee
Chimbombi, Director of Animal Health and Production, Ministry of
Agriculture, Gaborone:
Date of the report: 28 May 2004.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 15 Apr 2004.
Estimated date of primary infection: 1 Apr 2004.
Location of the outbreak: South-East district, Gaborone (24 deg 34
min 366 sec S - 25 deg 22 min 056 sec E).
Total number of equids in the outbreak: 30.
Total number of cases: 1.
Total number of deaths: 1.
Source of agent / origin of infection: unknown. African horse
sickness occurs sporadically in Botswana.
Control measures:
- control of arthropods;
- quarantine of the affected farm;
- movement control inside the country;
- vaccination.
